The President visited University Medical Center in Las Vegas to meet with patients and medical staff who were involved in the recent shooting incident. He praised the professionalism and bravery displayed by the doctors, nurses, and police department. The President also mentioned that he invited some of the patients to visit the White House. When asked about gun violence and the motive behind the shooting, the President declined to comment. He expressed admiration for the police department's response and mentioned that he would be visiting their headquarters next. The President also addressed recent comments made by Rex Tillerson, expressing his total confidence in him and calling the story "fake news."